---
description: Apply Clean Code and SOLID principles. Use for all TypeScript files across the monorepo.
globs: **/*.ts,**/*.tsx
alwaysApply: false
---

SOLID Principles:

- Single Responsibility: one class/function = one reason to change
- Open/Closed: extend via interfaces, not modification
- Liskov: subtypes must be substitutable for base types
- Interface Segregation: prefer many small interfaces over fat ones
- Dependency Inversion: depend on abstractions (interfaces), not concretions

Clean Code:

- Functions: max 20 lines, single level of abstraction
- Files: max 200 lines (split if larger)
- Parameters: max 3 per function (use object for more)
- Nesting: max 2 levels deep (extract early returns or helper functions)
- Comments: only explain WHY, never WHAT

Development Principles (ADR-014):

- TDD: write tests before implementation
- DRY: factorize systematically
- KISS: simplest solution that works
- YAGNI: don't code what's not needed now

Code Against Interfaces:

- Always program to an interface, never to an implementation
- Use dependency injection for all external dependencies
- Test via mocks of interfaces

Anti-Patterns:

- Avoid magic numbers/strings — use named constants or enums
- Avoid deep inheritance — prefer composition
- Avoid premature optimization
- Avoid dead code — remove unused imports, variables, functions
